  "6-43": (
    caption: [Modifications of the precursor rRNA by guide RNAs. (A) Two prominent covalent modifications made to rRNA; the differences from the initially incorporated nucleotide are indicated by red atoms. Pseudouridine is an isomer of uridine; the base has been “rotated” and is attached to the red C rather than to the red N of the sugar (compare to Figure 6–5B). (B) As indicated, snoRNAs determine the sites of modification by base-pairing to complementary sequences on the precursor rRNA. The snoRNAs are bound to proteins, and the complexes are called snoRNPs (small nucleolar ribonucleoproteins). The snoRNPs contain both the guide sequences and the enzymes that modify the rRNA. (A) P O O C C],
