  "6-62": (
    caption: [The recognition of a tRNA molecule by its aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase. For this tRNA (tRNAGln), specific nucleotides in both the anticodon (dark blue) and the amino acid–accepting arm (green) allow the correct tRNA to be recognized by the synthetase enzyme (yellow-green). The ATP molecule used in the coupling reaction is yellow. (Courtesy MBoC7 m6.58/6.62 of Tom Steitz. PDB code: 1QRS.)],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
