  "6-65": (
    caption: [A comparison of bacterial and eukaryotic ribosomes. Despite differences in the number and size of their rRNA and protein components, both bacterial and eukaryotic ribosomes have nearly the same structure and they function similarly. Although the 18S and 28S rRNAs of the eukaryotic ribosome contain many nucleotides not present in their bacterial counterparts, these extra nucleotides are present as multiple insertions that form extra domains and leave the basic structure of the rRNA largely unchanged.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
