  "6-73": (
    caption: [How proteins help shape ribosomal RNA. Shown here is the L15 protein in the large subunit of the bacterial ribosome. The globular domain of the protein lies on the surface of the ribosome, and an extended region penetrates deeply into the RNA core of the ribosome. The protein is shown in green and a portion of MBoC7 m6.69/6.73 the ribosomal RNA core is shown in blue. (From D. Klein et al., J. Mol. Biol. 340:141– 177, 2004. PDB code: 1S72.)],
